![contract](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42447141/206148473-b9f8feeb-01df-488a-93cd-def4e74921f2.JPG)


An infinite while loop is used in the above solidity example to update the `num` state variable, which should be forcefully stopped when the gas limit is exceeded (To fail the transaction quickly, I have chosen a gas limit of 1).

__Problem:__ The transaction is not failing and the webpage is getting stuck because of the loop.

__Expected:__ 

![error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42447141/206148901-debdfa21-1bbd-47d2-bd81-3c907a076fe7.JPG)

The transaction should fail, and a message should appear in the console. 


Browser: Firefox 107.0.1

Source Code:
```
// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0
pragma solidity 0.8.15;

contract MyContract {
    uint public num = 0;

    function forever() public {
        // Here we run a loop until all of the gas are spent and the transaction fails
        while (true) {
            num += 1;
        }
    }
}
```
